    <h1>Food waste a tough prob&#xAD;lem to crack</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201112/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-12"><time>2020-11-12</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Sin­ga­pore house­holds throw out over $340 mil­lion worth of food each year. And even be­fore it has a chance to reach con­sumers, a huge amount of pro­duce has al­ready been lost by farm­ers, im­porters and sell­ers.</p>
    <p>Egg farm Chew’s Agri­cul­ture is among those fight­ing back, by us­ing the one in 10 eggs there that would oth­er­wise end up in the bin.</p>
    <p>In a new se­ries start­ing this week­end,</p>
    <p>The Sun­day Times delves into the scale of the coun­try ’s food waste prob­lem, and looks at how busi­nesses, com­mu­ni­ties and in­di­vid­u­als are tack­ling it.</p>

